Valquiss <p><img src=http://www.traveling.freehosting.net/valquisssig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzeldagisravensoul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zeldagis Ravensoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/16/02 8:44:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1385.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   No topic header</span><hr size=1> Yes, this is a private message board.  You are here at Jaxy's pleasure.  [bold] However [/bold] I would hope the goal of this (or any other message board) is to facilitate the free expression of ideas.  If it's not, what is the point of ever bothering to express yourself?   Why go through the effort to post here under the pretense of freedom of expression when you can see you really have none because of the moderation/ownership? <br>
<br>
My suggestion isn't that the moderators need to be replaced, it's that they need to do their job, without ado, without taunting, and without ego.  Unfortunately, we've already seen that must be incredibly tough for some of the mod's, because mostly they [bold] enjoy [/bold] banning people with whom they disagree.  To me, that isn't right.  Agree or disagree, respect or disrespect, and even love or hate, people should be treated as equitably as possible by the mod's.  That's their job.  They aren't doing it very well, but that doesn't mean that they can't.<br>
<br>
I don't own the board, I don't run the board, and I certainly don't moderate the board, but that doesn't mean that my opinions (or everyone else's opinions) have no bearing or weight.  I would hope that the owner of the board would be more interested in the liberty of the board users to say their opinions, than whether they agree with the opinion.<br>
<br>
