PS: Please get out of my head. hehe That song started going through my mind as soon as I read the phrase &quot;I want a new...&quot; and I cant stand Hughey Lewis and the News.<br>
<br>
No way in hell I would ever be a mod over something like The Soapbox. Take out the politics, the histories, the lack of recognition or reimbursement, and the wide-open expanse of criticism whenever you make one of the 4 billion daily inevitably-controversial decisions you have to make, and the job is still a nightmare.<br>
<br>
Do I agree with every decision they make? Hell no. There are too many grey areas that they have to make decisions about daily for anyone to agree with them unilaterally. But whether I agree with them or not, I always respect them for the energy they invest into making this board, and by proxy the server, a superior environment in which to communicate ideas, opinions, and information in a mod(erately) civil manner.<br>
<br>
More people should try it before suggesting we get new ones. I think they're doing a good job.<br>
