<br>
And you know what happens if he doesn't?  He warns someone in private, then bans them, and then a bunch of you  know-it-all  hotshots spend a month complaining on the board how someone was banned without even a warning.  You can't have it both ways.  I think it's fair to give someone a public warning so all can see what lines have been crossed and what rules are being defended.<br>
<br>
The truth is, they don't have to give a warning, and they don't have to give explanations.  But they do.  You should appreciate that.<br>
<br>
Once again, this isn't a democracy.  Free Speech is not a right here.  You want free speech, go find yourself a nice street corner, or start your own board.  The thing is, you guys don't want the responsibility of running a board, so you keep coming here and then complaining about how this one is run.  Well, put you're money where your mouth is.  You think there's a better way, start your own board.  <br>
